                <h1>Heineken: Discover the Origins of Your Favorite Beer</h1>
                <p>Heineken beer originates from Amsterdam, Netherlands, where it was first brewed in 1864 by Gerard Adriaan Heineken. Known for its distinctive green bottle and a refreshing taste, Heineken has become a global symbol of quality lager. Today, it is enjoyed in over 190 countries worldwide, making it one of the most recognizable brands in beer.</p>
